The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Sunday, March 27, 2005 

 BRIEFS

 Alipurduar, March 26: Trouble erupted at Kalchini tea estate in Alipurduar sub-division, 750 km from Calcutta, when the manager refused to pay workers their salary. 

 The garden?s office superintendent, Deepak Dey Bhowmik, and Chanchal Roy Das, the in-charge of the factory, tried to pacify the crowd, who assaulted the duo and alleged that they had tried to sell 69 kg of tea without the manager?s permission.

 Police had to resort to lathicharge and reportedly fired in the air to disperse the mob.

 Midnapore: Five hundred people gheraoed Belpahari police station in West Midnapore on Saturday for over an hour to protest against two policemen who had allegedly beaten a man to death. Asit Dutta?s father Sanatan alleged that the police on Thursday arrested his son from Kashidanga village on the charge of stealing fish from a pond and battered him to death. 

 Chinsurah: A 21-year-old weaver in Hooghly?s Balagarh, about 70 km from Calcutta, was beaten to death on Friday when he tried to stop a group of intoxicated men from molesting a girl. ?Maheswar Rajbangshi jumped on the gang who then assaulted him. The youths picked up sticks and started beating him. Nobody came to his rescue,? said superintendent of police Supratim Sarkar. The weaver succumbed to injuries at Chinsurah hospital.




